Low Education High Consumption: Individuals with low education qualifications engaged in occupations generating high consumption patterns, usually in lower supervisory or managerial roles.
Low Education Median Consumption: Group characterized by low education qualifications and median consumption levels, often involved in intermediate or routine occupations.
Low Education Low Consumption: Individuals with low education qualifications predominantly in low-consuming jobs or long-term unemployment.
High Education: Individuals with high education qualifications, typically engaged in small entrepreneurship or similarly demanding roles.
Working & Unemployed: Group containing individuals with low education qualifications, showcasing varying occupational engagement with a mix of management roles and unemployment.
